HEADWORD: Brachiolaria
<hw>Brach`i*o*la"ri*a</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. L. <ets>brachiolum</ets> (<ets>bracch</ets>-), dim. of
<ets>brachium</ets> (<ets>bracch</ets>-) arm.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A peculiar early larval stage of certain starfishes, having a
bilateral structure, and swimming by means of bands of vibrating
cilia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

